use command compatible with windows 
use english in all your code
use english in all the logging messages (error ,info, warn)
use english in all the comments in your code
use a .gitignore pour ne pas stocker de données sensibles dans Git
use frontend directory to store all the frontend sources
use backend directory to store all the backend sources
use database directory to store all the database sources

--frontend rules:
use Vue.js V3 for the front end
don't use vue.js 2
don't use typescript
use Vue-i18n for internationalization of the front end
use modern UI
use subtle animations during transitions (example : hover over menus, content appearance).

--frontend CSS rules:
use Tailwind CSS v4 (not v3)
use @import "tailwindcss" syntax (not @tailwind directives)
use @theme directive for custom theme variables in Tailwind v4
use PrimeVue v4 for UI components with Aura theme preset
CSS layers order must be: theme, base, primevue, components, utilities
configure PrimeVue cssLayer option to match Tailwind layers order
Tailwind utilities classes (like ml-2, flex, gap-2) must override PrimeVue styles
use Tailwind utility classes for spacing, layout, and simple styling
use PrimeVue components for complex UI elements (DataTable, Dialog, Button, etc.)

--backend rules:
use node.js for the back end
use winston for logging with format YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss
do not use i18n in the back end 
do not add metadata within the api response except when it is a GET without query parameters

--backend ORM rules:
use Prisma as ORM for database access
Prisma client is configured in backend/src/config/prisma.js
service files using Prisma are named service.prisma.js (e.g., backend/src/api/v1/configuration_items/service.prisma.js)
use Prisma schema in backend/prisma/schema.prisma
use prisma migrate dev for database migrations
always use uuid for primary keys in Prisma models

--database rules:
use sql for the database
all objects in database have a uuid primary key
do not use serial id as primary key in the database
all attributes must start by rel_ when it refers to a key of an external object